# 14. 咲希の決意

Saki: Starting today, we can start practicing together! This is gonna be so awesome!
Shiho: Where were you thinking of having our first gig?
Saki: Our first...gig?
Shiho: Don't tell me you haven't thought that far. What are we going to be rehearsing for if not a gig?
Saki: Er... Our first show can be at...the school festival! Kind of clichéd, but I dig that kind of stuff!
Shiho: Oh well, I guess that's fine for starters. We've got to take this band stuff seriously, Saki.
Saki: But we only just got back together. Can't we take it easy for now?
Shiho: No. Once I let you get your foot in the door, your lack of discipline will affect everyone.
Saki: Ugh... You're being so harsh on me!
Ichika: Hehe. It's nice to see you two going at it again.
Ichika: Oh, we forgot to tell Miku and Luka that our band got bigger.
Saki: Oh, right! They had a hand in making this happen, so we should go and thank them!
Shiho: You've been practicing with them in SEKAI?
Saki: Yeah! They have been enormously helpful!
Saki: Maybe Hona would like to come along, too?
Shiho: That's...not likely.
Ichika: .....
Shiho: She still hasn't gotten over her junior high school trauma.
Saki: What trauma? What happened to her?
Shiho: I don't know the details. Just that her classmates had been ignoring her.
Saki: What?! But she's so nice, she makes friends wherever she goes. Why would they do that to her?
Shiho: Don't know. Whenever I tried to talk to her, she brushed me off saying not to worry.
Ichika: You were still talking to her back then?
Shiho: A bit. She looked really sad, so I wanted to find out why, but she always just clammed up.
Shiho: Didn't you notice how she was depressed all the time?
Ichika: .....
Shiho: Anyway, seems she couldn't stand being excluded, so now she follows her classmates around like a dog.
Ichika: Shiho, you're being mean.
Shiho: It peeves me that she changed so much. She used to be kind to everyone, but assertive. When someone was being mean, she'd call them out on it.
Shiho: But now? It's like she doesn't have a mind of her own anymore. If her classmates told her to bark and roll over, she would.
Shiho: It makes me so mad to see her like that.
Ichika: .....
Ichika: I spoke with her recently.
Saki & Shiho: Seriously?
Saki: That's heartbreaking...
Shiho: What she's doing is turning her back on us and her other friends because she can't face up to those bullies. That's not a solution!
Ichika: You have to understand that she's scared.
Ichika: Besides, she's the gentle type. She worries about upsetting people around her.
Shiho: Yeah, right. But she didn't care about upsetting you or Saki?!
Shiho: ...Look, I'm sorry. I just can't understand why Honami's being like this.
Shiho: Although I guess I can't really talk...
Ichika: Shiho...
Saki: Hona's always been super kind.
Saki: Shiho, remember when that hat you really liked fell into the river and Honami jumped in to get it for you? Her clothes got all wet, but she didn't hesitate for a moment!
Shiho: ...Yeah.
Saki: She puts others' needs before her own.
Ichika: .....
Saki: I see now what we should do.
Saki: We should give up on getting her to join the band.
Ichika: What?!
Shiho: Saki, are you serious?
Saki: Yeah. This will be an act of kindness from me to her.
Saki: Heh, I guess I kinda sound full of myself.
Saki: But I don't want to cause her any more trouble.
Saki: I wish I could tell her that I'll always be her friend, no matter what...
Saki: But I wasn't there for her when she needed me before, so it would just sound like an empty promise.
Shiho: .....
Ichika: I'm sorry... I told you about the bullying because I thought we could still do something now. I didn't mean to make you feel bad about what happened...
Saki: No worries, I get it.
Saki: Anyway, Hona is now getting along with her classmates.
Saki: I don't think it would be right for us to throw a spanner in the works because we think our friendship should matter more to her.
Saki: We have to respect her choices.
Saki: Moving on, we should get some practice done! Let's go over to Miku's place!
Shiho: .....
